SIMPLE: emulous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Emulous
<hw>Em"u*lous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>aemulus</ets>. See <er>Emulate</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Ambitiously desirous to equal or even to excel another; eager to
emulate or vie with another; desirous of like excellence with another;
-- with <xex>of</xex>; <as>as, <ex>emulous</ex> of another's example or
virtues</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Vying with; rivaling; hence, contentious,
envious.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Emulous</xex> Carthage.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>B.
Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Emulous</qex> missions 'mongst the gods.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Emulously</ent>⟦br⟧
